cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

The paper discusses a shared task related to natural language processing and information retrieval, specifically identifying text spans in a document being referenced by a citation. This falls under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL). The use of topic models and word embeddings also suggests a focus on unsupervised learning, which is commonly studied in these sub-categories.
